723949f.title: Manhattan: Wall Street - Water Street
723949f.text:
Wall Street and environs, west from Water Street, showing
office structures foraing the financial district. The skyscraper
under construction is tne 70 storied Bank of Manhattan at No. 40
Vall Street. To the left is the 35 story Wall and lanover Building.
To the right are, the 26-story building (No. 62-67 Pine Street) at
the rear of No. 60 Wall Street (H.L. Dougherty and Company), the
domed Singer Building, the massive Equitable Building, the modern
No. 1 Cedar Street, the Transportation Building and the ornate Wool-
worth Building. Note on Wall Street the glimpses of the Bankers
Trust Company (pyramidal tower), the Electric Bond and Share Building
and the New York 3tock Exchange Building. The triangular structures
in the left foreground are respectively the 15 storied Beaver Building
and the 25 story Munson S.S. Line Building. Obscuring the lower
portions of the latter is the 12 story Orient Building.
1929

723951f-a.text:
